<!--
  obelisk note (2026-05-20):
  All <inertial> blocks have been resynchronized to match the MJCF in
    obelisk_ws/src/robots/themis_description/mujoco/themis_29dof.xml
  which in turn matches themis_rl's hand-authored sim model.  See
    docs/plans/themis_inertia_discrepancies.md
  for the reasoning (notably the UPPERARM principal moments where the
  csv-to-urdf output disagrees with the physics by 10x).

  The transform was applied automatically by
    docs/plans/sync_urdf_to_mjcf.py
  which rotates each MJCF body-frame inertial into the URDF's body frame
  via M = R_mjcf_world^T @ R_urdf_world per body.  BASE_LINK is also
  patched (MuJoCo's URDF importer doesn't expose it as a body, so the
  script can't reach it; it's hand-edited to match the MJCF's BASE_LINK
  inertial.)

  Regenerating from CAD will overwrite these changes; re-run
  sync_urdf_to_mjcf.py afterwards if needed.

  Other hand edits (also 2026-05-20):
    * `package://themis_description/meshes/` was changed to `../meshes/`
      so IsaacLab's URDF→USD converter (which resolves meshes relative to
      the URDF file, not via ROS resolver) finds them without ROS context.
    * FOOT_R and FOOT_L: mesh `<collision>` blocks commented out and
      replaced with a single `<box>` collision spanning the foot
      footprint.  Matches the MJCF box geom in themis_29dof.xml.
    * LOWERWRIST_R and LOWERWRIST_L: mesh `<collision>` commented out
      and replaced with a `<sphere>` collision at the hand contact point
      (mirrors the MJCF `hand_contact_R/L` geoms).
-->

